class_name RnDEngine
## Version: S40.13 — P4 EFFECT ACCESSOR LAYER + 4 clusters wired. Added team-aware get_rnd_bonus /
##   get_rnd_bonus_sum / as_gain / as_reduction + grouped getters (perf_bonus, reliability_bonus,
##   fatigue_bonus, economy_*). Wired: PERFORMANCE→lap time, RELIABILITY→condition loss,
##   FATIGUE→in-race fitness drop, ECONOMY→weekly maintenance/passive income. tax_reduction accessor
##   ready but no tax system to hook yet; reliability routed to wear (no mid-race failure roll yet).
## Version: S40.12 — P4 benefit coherence: SP_OST_6 (tactical_error_reduction) had value 0 (inert) →
##   set 0.15. Rewrote 7 qualitative descs to state their actual numbers (e.g. "Major boost"→"+10%
##   concentration", "Unlocks in-house major repairs"→"+15% in-house repair capability", the 3 pit-stop
##   tiers → -1/-2/-3%). Every P4 now has a non-zero value AND a numeric desc. NOTE: most P4 effect
##   keys are stored (rnd_bonuses) but not yet READ by the sim/economy — wiring each effect into its
##   system is a separate task; this only makes the data sane + player-legible.
## Version: S40.10 — Fitness Clinic max_level 109→11 alignment: its 4 P4 gates remapped ceil(old/10)
##   → 3/6/8/11 (legal vs new cap); RP/CR/weeks/Studio untouched from the S40.8 re-cost.
## Version: S40.8 — P4 SPECIAL PROJECTS RE-COST (all 100). RP/CR/Weeks/Required_RnD_Studio_Level are
##   now generated by a building-depth curve × gameplay-impact weight: depth = min_building_level /
##   building_max_level, cost = lerp(min,max, depth^2.2) × impact_mult (tier 1-5 → ×0.25..1.4). Fixes
##   the premature values: 9 RP monotonicity reversals, 20× within-gate spread, 4 illegal building
##   gates (Merchandise L7>max5, clamped), and Studio reqs up to 60 (Studio caps at 27 → clamped 1-27).
##   Hero projects (impact-5 + deep: overtaking, pit mastery, DNF-reduction) intentionally overshoot
##   toward ~210k RP. Coherent costs also repair the RP storage cap (dyn term now scales with level
##   instead of a flat 103k). Generator: tools/p4_recost.py (dry-run-first, snapshots a .bak).
## Version: S40.0 — LEAD DESIGNER REWORK (Brainstorm thread #6), engine layer. Capacity is now the
##   R&D Studio LEVEL (N design lines), NOT a designer head-count. ONE Lead Designer per team oversees
##   all lines. Each designer has a comfortable line count C = f(overall_skill) (locked curve, headless
##   pass: C_MAX=18, γ=1.55 → skill44≈5 lines, skill76≈12, skill100≈18). Within C → full effectiveness;
##   beyond C → SOFT, no-ceiling convex penalty on BOTH quality (designer effective stats scale down)
##   AND speed (the line's weeks stretch up). Dynamic survivor rule: no Studio → no lines → no R&D
##   (a built-but-designerless Studio = idle lines, a legible failure state). The old hard
##   "Designer Busy" one-task-per-designer block is REPLACED by line-capacity accounting: a Lead may
##   drive multiple lines up to the Studio level and eat the over-stretch penalty past C. EVERY R&D
##   project occupies one line while running — P1/P2/P3 racing blueprints, P4 Special Projects, and
##   P5 commercial-model blueprints (assembly-Factory pipeline, NOT CNC). All take the weeks-stretch
##   + count against capacity; the QUALITY penalty applies to P1/P3 only (they have a per-part design
##   stat) — P4/P5 take no quality hit by design. The advisor proposes P1-3 only (P4/P5 stay
##   deliberate player picks). Balance
##   constants live in ONE block (LEAD DESIGNER TUNING) for the Phase-5 pass. Proposal/advisor UX is
##   in the new LeadDesignerProposalEngine (mirrors TPProposalEngine). JSON surgery (3098→172+~100 FAs)
##   is a SEPARATE later session — this layer works on today's data unchanged (each team's designers
##   still load; capacity/penalty key off the Studio + the assigned Lead).
## Version: S39.7 — Facelift/Next-Gen R&D mini-projects complete here → apply refresh + queue rename popup
## Version: S39.5 — P5 research gate: removed the race-the-championship requirement (Studio level only)
